# Deploy command

When the user says **deploy** (or "ship it", "release now", "push to production"), run the full pipeline — do not only commit or only push.

## Before deploy

1. Ensure `package.json` version matches `changelog.json` latest entry (run `npm run check:version`).
2. If version/changelog are out of sync, bump patch in `package.json`, add a new first entry in `changelog.json` with user-facing changes, then deploy.
3. Run unit tests if code changed since last test: `npm run test:unit`.

## Deploy (single command)

```bash
npm run deploy
```

This runs [`scripts/deploy.mjs`](scripts/deploy.mjs) which:

1. Verifies release consistency
2. Commits `package.json` + `changelog.json` if needed (`chore(release): vX.Y.Z`)
3. Pushes the app repo to `origin`
4. Runs `sync-website.mjs` — updates `custody-note-website/data/releases.json`, commits, pushes → **Vercel auto-deploys custodynote.com**
5. Re-pushes the release tag to trigger **Release and deploy** (Windows + Mac installers on GitHub)

## Do not

- Use `mailto:` or ad-hoc git pushes without changelog sync
- Skip website sync unless user explicitly says `--skip-website-sync`
- Run `electron-builder` locally for deploy — CI builds installers on tag push
- Edit the plan file when executing deploy

## After deploy

Report: version shipped, app push status, website sync status, link to GitHub Actions "Release and deploy" workflow.
